race.comment: GRINZINGER BISHOP (2) was dominant at Gawler last time, leading throughout and never letting them in. Has the pace to offset the wide alley and looks set to give another bold sight over the longer trip. Expect him to take plenty of catching again. FOX GEM (3) chased hard behind GRINZINGER BISHOP last start and stuck on gamely. Meets the winner better at the weights this time and is ready to peak over a proven winning trip. THINKINGNINTYNINE (7) has tactical speed and should roll forward again, giving himself every chance. On the quick back-up and will be in this for a long way. HARLEY'N'ROSE (8) improved sharply last time when stepping up in trip. Open to further progress and is among the winning hopes. KIRKLISTON BLU (4) doesn't win often but is consistently around the mark. Only needs to hold his form to be right in the finish.
